f=Engineering/quinn/marketplace/webapp-testing/SKILL.md · h1:Web Application Testing=test local web applications, write native Python Playwright scripts. **Helper Scripts Available**: · h1:Web Application Testing=`scripts/with_server.py` Manages server lifecycle (supports multiple servers) · h1:Web Application Testing=**Always run scripts `--help` first** see usage. read source until you try running script first find customized solution abslutely necessary. scripts large thus pollute your context window. They exist called directly black-box scripts rather ingested your context window. · h2:Decision Tree: Choosing Your Approach=`User task → Is it static HTML? \· ├─ Yes → Read HTML file directly to identify selectors \· │         ├─ Success → Write Playwright script using selectors \· │         └─ Fails/Incomplete → Treat as dynamic (below) \· │` · h2:Example: Using with_server.py=`python scripts/with_server.py --server "npm run dev" --port 5173 -- python your_automation.py` · h2:Example: Using with_server.py=`python scripts/with_server.py \ \· --server "cd backend && python server.py" --port 3000 \ \· --server "cd frontend && npm run dev" --port 5173 \ \· -- python your_automation.py` · h2:Example: Using with_server.py=`from playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright \·  \· with sync_playwright() as p: \· browser = p.chromium.launch(headless=True) # Always launch chromium in headless mode \· page = browser.new_page()` · h2:Example: Using with_server.py=start server, run `--help` first, use helper: **Single server:** **Multiple servers (e.g., backend frontend):** create automation script, include Playwright logic (servers managed automatically): · h2:Reconnaissance-Then-Action Pattern=`page.screenshot(path='/tmp/inspect.png', full_page=True) \· content = page.content() \· page.locator('button').all()` · h2:Reconnaissance-Then-Action Pattern=**Inspect rendered DOM**: **Identify selectors** inspection results **Execute actions** using discovered selectors · h2:Common Pitfall=**Don't** inspect DOM before waiting `networkidle` dynamic apps **Do** wait `page.wait_for_load_state('networkidle')` before inspection · h2:Best Practices=**Use bundled scripts black boxes** accomplish task, consider whether one scripts available `scripts/` help. scripts handle common, complex workflows reliably without cluttering context window. Use `--help` see usage, invoke directly., Use `sync_playwright()` synchronous scripts, Always close browser done, Use descriptive selectors: `text=`, `role=`, CSS selectors, IDs, Add appropriate waits: `page.wait_for_selector()` `page.wait_for_timeout()` · h2:Reference Files=**examples/** Examples showing common patterns:, `element_discovery.py` Discovering buttons, links, inputs page, `static_html_automation.py` Using file:// URLs local HTML, `console_logging.py` Capturing console logs during automation